article.headline: Kent St. 81, Toledo 52
article.story: KENT, Ohio -- Tyree Evans scored 14 points and Mike McKee added four decisive 3-pointers just before halftime to lead Kent State past Toledo 81-52 Tuesday night. McKee's third 3-pointer put Kent State (11-11, 4-4 Mid-American) ahead 36-24 with 34 seconds left in the half and gave the Golden Flashes a double-digit lead they wouldn't relinquish. He made another 3-pointer with four seconds remaining until intermission. Tyrone Kent led Toledo (4-18, 2-6) with 17 points, Justin Anyijong added 13 points and nine rebounds and Larry Bastfield scored 10. Julian Sullinger scored 12 points for Kent State, which shot 61.5 percent in the second half as the Golden Flashes ran up their lead
